{"word":"H3669 - כְּנַעַנִי - Kᵉnaʻanîy - ken-ah-an-ee' - Canaanite","slug":"H3669","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">כְּנַעַנִי</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>Kᵉnaʻanîy"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>ken-ah-an-ee'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Canaanite"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05DB;&#x05BC;&#x05E0;&#x05E2;&#x05E0;&#x05D9; - k<sup>e</sup>na&#x201B;an&#x0131;&#x0302;y</b> - <i>ken-ah-an-ee'</i><p/>Patrial from <a href=\"#/H3667\">H3667</a>; a <i>Kenaanite</i> or inhabitant of Kenaan; by implication a <i>pedlar</i> (the Cananites standing for their neighbors the Ishmaelites, who conducted mercantile caravans): - Canaanite, merchant, trafficker."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H3665\">H3665</a>, <a href=\"#/H3666\">H3666</a>, <a href=\"#/H3667\">H3667</a>, <a href=\"#/H3668\">H3668</a>"}]}